{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":14482,"record_hash":"sha256:10520193d0e0a424a9582e2ae3f7286cf49d8d6da5dbbc4c8e0e566fab1c9a5d","timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:54:45.972Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 28dbee\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1135\nOutput:\n    C --> D[\"Resolve target\"]\n    D --> E[\"Select agent collector\"]\n    E --> F[\"Locate session source\"]\n    F --> G[\"Read transcript records\"]\n    G --> H[\"Apply capture cursor\"]\n    H --> I[\"Normalize records\"]\n    I --> J[\"Write GitButler GitMeta session data\"]\n    J --> K[\"Return command output\"]\n```\n\n## Target Resolution\n\nTarget resolution should be conservative.\n\nFor the POC:\n\n1. Use the explicit `--target` value when present.\n2. Otherwise use `project`.\n3. Report that no branch/commit target was inferred.\n\nFor later milestones:\n\n1. Use a hook-provided target when a future hook payload includes one.\n2. Use the current branch as `branch:<name>` only when repository state is\n   unambiguous.\n3. Fall back to `project` and report that no branch/commit target was inferred.\n\nCommit targets should require explicit commit ids or commit ids produced by a\nGitButler operation. A session may touch many commits, and guessing from `HEAD`\nwould create misleading provenance.\n\n## Agent Collection\n\nFor the POC, use a closed `Agent` enum and explicit parser branches for Codex\nand Claude. Each branch reads the same byte snapshot and returns the shared\ntranscript record shape used by the GitMeta writer. It should not write GitMeta.\n\nThe initial Codex and Claude collectors should only use `transcript_path`.\n\nLater, the Codex collector can use this priority order:\n\n1. explicit `transcript_path`\n2. explicit `session_id`\n3. environment session id such as `CODEX_THREAD_ID`\n4. recent Codex session files under known session directories filtered by repo\n   cwd\n\nFuture Codex discovery should resolve the session root from `CODEX_HOME` first,\nthen from the user's home directory joined with `.codex`. The expected CLI\ntranscript layout is:\n\n```text\n$[REDACTED:entropy]*.jsonl\n```\n\nTreat this as adapter knowledge, not generic capture logic. The collector should\nscan a narrow recent window, inspect enough JSONL to\n[TRUNCATED]\nes: Codex and Claude. Later, if more agents need different\nbehaviors, evolve toward small optional capabilities such as transcript\npreparation, native transcript reading, modified-file extraction, and\nresume-command formatting. Keep those capabilities at the adapter boundary; the\nGitMeta writer should stay agent-agnostic.\n\n## GitMeta Writer\n\nThe writer should be the only code that depends directly on `git-meta-lib`.\nDo not reimplement a custom Git metadata branch/ref store in GitButler; that is\nGitMeta's job. Systems like Entire may need their own Go storage layer, but this\nPOC should stay on the Rust `git-meta-lib` API.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n- open `git_meta_lib::Session`\n- resolve a `git_meta_lib::Target`\n- write GitButler session keys under `gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*`\n- maintain `gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>`\n- append redacted transcript envelopes to\n  `gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:transcript`\n- keep metadata hashes and transcript envelope hashes separate so transcript\n  appends remain idempotent after partial writes or missing list state\n- write GitButler-specific source provenance keys\n- optionally call `Session::serialize()` in a later debug/sync milestone, not in the first POC\n\nThe writer should return a write report rather than printing.\n\n## Privacy Boundary\n\nCapture is not published by the command. The POC writes shareable-ready\n`gitbutler:*` keys but does not call GitMeta serialize, push, fetch, or sync.\n\nEven local capture should be treated as sensitive: prompts can contain secrets,\nprivate code, customer context, or pasted credentials. The POC should redact\nhigh-entropy strings, UUID-shaped values, and random-looking long hex strings\nbefore storing transcript envelopes. It should not store full transcript paths,\ncwd values, branch names, or raw provider session ids. Serialization and push\nintegration should be added only after destination filters and user-facing\nprivacy behavior are defined.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nExpected dependencies:\n\n- `git-meta-lib`\n- `serde`\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:54:45.972Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}